Reviews.Title: Good for the kids
Reviews.Author: A. Cowan
Reviews.Content: I got this tablet for the kids and they play games on it almost every day.  It also takes good pictures and video.  We like it so far.

Reviews.Title: Not bad for the price (for a kid)
Reviews.Author: Kadin C.
Reviews.Content: Got it for my 13 yr old after he broke his old one. Nice clear screen. It does not have the Google Play Store. It does offer an app store of sorts, but doesn't have as many apps. You cannot use 2 apps at the same time. So if you want to listen to a video on You Tube and Facebook at the same time, its not happening. The Facebook app and a few others crash a lot. The on screen keyboard will not work if the tablet is long ways, only sideways - which makes it harder to type as the keys are farther apart.Overall, the cons can be dealt with for the price - for a kid. If your an adult, I would recommend spending $20 bucks more and getting something of better quality and the Play Store!

Reviews.Title: Worthless IMO
Reviews.Author: Amazon Customer
Reviews.Content: I couldn't get Facebook to work, I couldn't get Dishanywhere to work, I couldn't get netflix to work. I couldn't get anything to work really.  It's a cheap price but if nothing works what is the point?  Froze for me constantly, slow downloads between freezes even with a super fast internet connection.  Also this does not have the Play Store installed, that should tell you something right there.

Reviews.Title: Slow
Reviews.Author: Pen Name
Reviews.Content: it's ok kinda slow and some app doesn't even work and there is no google play store!!!! Sometimes it freezes and app crashes a lot

Reviews.Title: spend a little more money for something that is going to last
Reviews.Author: Erika
Reviews.Content: I was looking for a tablet for my 8 year old kid. Something cheap just for entertainment.. This wasn't it....it over heated very quickly and had to be returned within 1 week.

Reviews.Title: Great value
Reviews.Author: Kenneth Scope
Reviews.Content: It is not an iPad, but it is not as expensive as the iPad either. I could not believe you could get a tablet for under $50. I only bought it to use it as an additional controller of my SONOS system (a Wireless Hi-Fi speaker/hometheater system). The SONOS app works with Android too. So I did not want to buy an expensive iPad or iPod Touch. I normally control my SONOS from my iPhone but wanted to have an additional inexpensive way to control it wirelessly. Astro Queo 7" does not have the latest Android OS, but I do not mind it for the use. I have not surfed much on it, but I don't see anything wrong surfing the net, checking the Google App store, Facebook and checking mail. I think that for such a low price, this tablet is a bargain.I noticed the battery has relatively low duration, compared to other similar devices, but not tremendously bad. You can probably do most of normal tasks during a whole day in one charge. The screen resolution is not as good as that of an iPad, but again, for this price, it is more than enough. The interface is a bit clumky, but nothing that would make you suffer.I personally don't find a lot of room between my ultra-slim MacBook Air and my iPhone, so I have not decided to buy a tablet yet. But I do enjoy using my daughter's iPad when laying on the couch or in bed. Not enough to make me shed the few hundreds. But the Astro Queo 7" may even prevent me from ever deciding to spend so much money on an iPad. But if you do not have any Mac laptop or iPhone, you'll probably better off with an iPad.
